The paper deals with problems related to graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the problem of finding mutually induced paths in a graph. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Discrete Structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the fixed-parameter tractability of the problem, which is a topic in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper mentions the complexity of the problem in terms of kernelization, which is a topic in Complexity Theory (cs.CC).
